RealTimeResultGroupDefinition.SqlString: SELECT Port.Name AS 'Port Name', ProbeFrameResponseConfig.Name AS 'Name', FrameResponseResults.MatchedRxFrameCount AS 'Matched Received Frame Count (Frames)', FrameResponseResults.MatchedRxFrameRate AS 'Matched Received Frame Rate (frames/s) (fps)', FrameResponseResults.TxFrameCount AS 'Transmitted Frame Count (Frames)' FROM ProbeFrameResponseConfig, Port, FrameResponseResults, Probe WHERE ( Probe.ParentHnd = Port.Handle AND ProbeFrameResponseConfig.ParentHnd = Probe.Handle AND FrameResponseResults.ParentHnd = ProbeFrameResponseConfig.Handle AND ProbeFrameResponseConfig.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND Port.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND FrameResponseResults.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND Probe.DataSetId = @DataSetId ) UNION SELECT ExternalDevicePort.Name AS 'Port Name', ProbeFrameResponseConfig.Name AS 'Name', FrameResponseResults.MatchedRxFrameCount AS 'Matched Received Frame Count (Frames)', FrameResponseResults.MatchedRxFrameRate AS 'Matched Received Frame Rate (frames/s) (fps)', FrameResponseResults.TxFrameCount AS 'Transmitted Frame Count (Frames)' FROM ProbeFrameResponseConfig, ExternalDevicePort, FrameResponseResults, Port, Probe WHERE ( Probe.ParentHnd = Port.Handle AND ProbeFrameResponseConfig.ParentHnd = Probe.Handle AND FrameResponseResults.ParentHnd = ProbeFrameResponseConfig.Handle AND ProbeFrameResponseConfig.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND ExternalDevicePort.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND FrameResponseResults.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND Port.DataSetId = @DataSetId AND Probe.DataSetId = @DataSetId )
